			<ns0:name>mseaborn@chromium.org</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/mseaborn@chromium.org/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Victor wrote:
&gt; It's Ok to have Chrome dependency in optional parts of Native
&gt; Client - for example if Native Client will provide additional
&gt; facilities to Chrome extension writers this part can depend on
&gt; Chrome.

The existing dependency *is* conditional - otherwise the
standalone build wouldn't work.  But that might not be obvious
from the code (so I suggest addressing
http://code.google.com/p/nativeclient/issues/detail?id=496).

The dependency is not so much on the Chromium browser as on the
Chromium sandbox.  It just happens that the Chromium sandbox
hasn't been split out from Chromium, though I think it would be
good to do so.
